The evidence with the title 'Concealed carry in the United States - Wikipedia ' says Concealed carry or carrying a concealed weapon (ccw), is the practice of carrying a weapon (such as a handgun) in public in a concealed manner, either on one's person or in close proximity. Not all weapons that fall under CCW laws are lethal.  ... There is no federal statutory law concerning the issuance of concealed-carry ... 
